|| 1 || 1 || 10 || 6 || +4 || 2\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | Saint Mary's Huskies   || 2 || 1 || 1 || 6 || 8 || -2 || 2\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | McGill Redmen          || 2 || 1 || 1 || 5 || 7 || -2 || 2\n|}\n\nNote: The Western Mustangs are the second team, in the expanded 6-team format, to advance to the championship final with a 1\u20131 record. The Alberta Golden Bears were the first team to advanced to the finals with a 1\u20131 record, which occurred the previous season in Moncton.\n\n==Championship Final==\n{{IceHockeybox\n| bg          = #eeeeee\n| date        = March 29, 2010\n| time        = 7:00 PM (EST)<br>[[Rogers Sportsnet]]\n| team1       =''' #4 [[UNB Varsity Reds]]''' (H)\n| team2       = #3 [[Western Mustangs]] (V)\n| score       = 4-2\n| periods     = (1\u20130, 1\u20131, 2\u20131)\n| reference   = https://www.thunderwolveshockey.com/article/unb-wins-university-cup?archive=2008-2009\n| goalie1     = Travis Fullerton (3-0-0)\n| goalie2     = Brad Topping (1-2-0)\n| progression = 1-0<br>2-0<br>2-1<br>2-2<br>3-2<br>4-2\n| goals1      = L. MacIntosh (unassisted) - 18:58<br>J-S. Dickson (D. Bowman, J. Harty) - 21:02<br><br><br> L. MacIntosh (K. Bailey, J. Cuddihy) 50:24<br>\n L. MacIntosh (K. Bailey) 59:14 EN<br>\n| goals2      = <br><br>28:57 - P. Ouellet (J. McCann)<br>41:13 - K. Baker (J. Martens, J. Furlong) \n| official    = Derek Zalaski\n| official2   = \n| linesman    = Nigel Black\n| linesman2   = Matt Traub\n| stadium     = [[Fort William Gardens]], [[Thunder Bay, Ontario|Thunder Bay]]\n| attendance  = 2,715 \n| penalties1  = 4 for 8\n| penalties2  = 3 for 6\n| shots1      = (10, 10, 17) - 37\n| shots2      = 30 - (1, 18, 11)\n}}\n\n==Tournament All-Stars==\n[[Lachlan MacIntosh]], a forward from the UNB Varsity Reds, was selected as the Major W.J. 'Danny' McLeod Award for CIS University Cup MVP. He had a hat-trick in the Gold Medal final to finish with 5G+1A for 6 Points, tying the tournament lead with teammate Kyle Baily 1G+5A, and was UNB's Game MVP in the Finals as well as in their tournament opener versus Alberta on Thursday.\n\nJoining MacIntosh on the tournament all-star team were:<ref>UNB Wins University Cup https://www.thunderwolveshockey.com/article/unb-wins-university-cup?archive=2008-2009</ref>\n\nGoaltender: Travis Fullerton, UNB Varsity Reds<br>\nDefenseman: Dustin Friesen, UNB Varsity Reds<br>\nDefenseman: Chris Petrow, Western Mustangs<br>\nForward: Kyle Bailey, UNB Varsity Reds<br>\nForward: Joe McCann, Western Mustangs\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{CIS men's ice hockey}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2010 CIS University Cup}}\n[[Category:U Sports ice hockey]]\n[[Category:2009\u201310 in Canadian ice hockey|University Cup, 2010]]\n", "name_user": "Jcoolbro", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 - fix /WP:WCWproject (Missing end bold/italic)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2009_CIS_University_Cup"}
{"title_page": "14th Government of Slovenia", "text_new": "{{Infobox government cabinet\n|cabinet_name              = 14th Government of the Republic of Slovenia\n|former_members_number     =\n|previous                  = [[13th Government of Slovenia]]\n|outgoing_formation        =\n|incoming_formation        =\n|budget                    =\n|legislature_term          = [[8th National Assembly of the Republic of Slovenia|8th National Assembly]]\n|election                  = [[2018 Slovenian parliamentary election|2018 election]]\n|opposition_leader         = Not an official position<br>[[Marjan \u0160arec]] (LM\u0160)<br>[[Dejan \u017didan]] (SD)<br>[[Luka Mesec]] (Levica)<br>[[Alenka Bratu\u0161ek]] (SAB)<br>[[Zmago Jelin\u010di\u010d Plemeniti]] (SNS)\n|opposition_party          = [[List of Marjan \u0160arec|LM\u0160]]<br>[[Social Democrats (Slovenia)|SD]]<br>[[The Left (Slovenia)|Levica]]<br>[[Party of Alenka Bratu\u0161ek|SAB]]<br>[[Slovenian National Party|SNS]] (support)\n|legislature_status        = [[Centre-right politics|Centre-right]] [[majority government]]<br />{{Composition bar|47|90|grey}}\n|political_party           = [[Slovenian Democratic Party|SDS]]<br>[[Modern Centre Party|SMC]]<br>[[New Slovenia|NSi]]<br>[[Democratic Party of Pensioners of Slovenia|DeSUS]]\n|total_number              =16\n|members_number            = PM + 16 ministers\n|cabinet_type              =\n|state_head                = [[President of Slovenia|President]] [[Borut Pahor]] (SD)\n|deputy_government_head    = [[Prime minister of Slovenia#Deputy prime minister|Deputy Prime Ministers]]<br>[[Zdravko Po\u010dival\u0161ek]] (SMC)<br>[[Matej Tonin]] (NSi)<br>[[Aleksandra Pivec]] (DeSUS)\n|government_head_history   =\n|government_head           = [[Prime Minister of Slovenia|Prime Minister]] [[Janez Jan\u0161a]] (SDS)\n|date_dissolved            =\n|date_formed               = 13 March 2020\n|caption                   =\n|image_size                = 230px\n|image                     = Logo-rs-vrs.png\n|incumbent                 =\n|flag_border               = true\n|flag                      = Flag_of_Slovenia.svg\n|jurisdiction              = Republic of Slovenia\n|cabinet_number            = 14th\n|successor                 = \n|opposition_cabinet=None}}\n\n{{Politics of Slovenia}}\n\nThe '''14th Government of Slovenia''' was formed following the resignation of Prime Minister of the [[13th Government of Slovenia|13th Government]] [[Marjan \u0160arec]] in January 2020. [[Janez Jan\u0161a]] of [[Slovenian Democratic Party]] formed a coallition with [[Modern Centre Party]], [[New Slovenia]], and [[Democratic Party of Pensioners of Slovenia]]. The government was confirmed on 13 March 2020, amidst the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Slovenia|coronavirus outbreak]].\n\n<br />\n\n== Government formation ==\nOn 27 January 2020 Prime Minister [[Marjan \u0160arec]] (LM\u0160) resigned following the resignation of the Finance Minister [[Andrej Bertoncelj]] (LM\u0160) and previously announced resignation of Minister of Health [[Ale\u0161 \u0160abeder]] (LM\u0160) due to disagreements around new healthcare legislation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtvslo.si/slovenija/po-sarcevem-odstopu-prvaki-strank-o-scenarijih-razpleta-najnovejse-politicne-krize/512760|title=Po \u0160ar\u010devem odstopu: prvaki strank o scenarijih razpleta najnovej\u0161e politi\u010dne krize|website=RTVSLO.si|language=sl|access-date=2020-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226140330/https://www.rtvslo.si/slovenija/po-sarcevem-odstopu-prvaki-strank-o-scenarijih-razpleta-najnovejse-politicne-krize/512760|archive-date=2020-02-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February 2020 President Pahor concluded the second round of consultations with political parties. Parties that are forming the new government confirmed the coalition agreement which was signed on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.24ur.com/novice/slovenija/neuradno-naj-bi-sds-smc-nsi-in-desus-sklenili-dogovor-o-novi-vladi.html|title=DeSUS, NSi in SMC potrdili vstop v Jan\u0161evo vlado|website=www.24ur.com|language=sl|access-date=2020-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226170045/https://www.24ur.com/novice/slovenija/neuradno-naj-bi-sds-smc-nsi-in-desus-sklenili-dogovor-o-novi-vladi.html|archive-date=2020-02-26|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JJansaSDS/status/1232615911925977089|title=ZA BLAGINJO SLOVENIJE pic.twitter.com/J3XxS0jDla|last=Jan\u0161a|first=Janez|date=2020-02-26|website=@JJansaSDS|language=sl|access-date=2020-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226105559/https://twitter.com/JJansaSDS/status/1232615911925977089|archive-date=2020-02-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February 2020 [[President of Slovenia|President of the Republic]] [[Borut Pahor]] proposed to the National Assembly [[Janez Jan\u0161a]] as candidate for Prime Minister.<ref>https://imss.dz-rs.si/IMiS/ImisAdmin.nsf/ImisnetAgent?OpenAgent&2&DZ-MSS-01/35be1f4654d42d4bc3a5488b60820e76b6a67406768e8f4e5802f397f6668633</ref>\n\nOn 3 March 2020 [[Janez Jan\u0161a]] was elected Prime Minister with 52 votes, which means 3 opposition MPs voted for him, most probably MPs of [[Slovenian National Party|SNS]]. [[Jani Ivanu\u0161a]] (SNS) also publicly stated he would support Jan\u0161a.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rtvslo.si/slovenija/janez-jansa-novi-predsednik-vlade-dobil-je-52-poslanskih-glasov/516027|title=Janez Jan\u0161a novi predsednik vlade, dobil je 52 poslanskih glasov|website=RTVSLO.si|language=sl|access-date=2020-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303162212/https://www.rtvslo.si/slovenija/janez-jansa-novi-predsednik-vlade-dobil-je-52-poslanskih-glasov/516027|archive-date=2020-03-03|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March 2020 Prime Minister-elect [[Janez Jan\u0161a]] proposed to the National Assembly the list of candidates for ministers. Hearings took place from 10 until 13 March 2020. Ministers of the 13th Government worked closely with the incoming formation in the time of transition to inform incoming ministers on the situation related to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus outbreak]]. Such coordination has not happened before. Both formations had a joint meeting on 9 March 2020. On 12 March 2020 outgoing Minister of Health [[Ale\u0161 \u0160abeder]] declared epidemic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtvslo.si/zdravje/novi-koronavirus/sabeder-96-potrjenih-primerov-v-sloveniji-razglasili-epidemijo/516916|title=\u0160abeder: 96 potrjenih primerov, v Sloveniji razglasili epidemijo|website=www.rtvslo.si|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> Prime Minister-elect was critical of some decision taken by the outgoing formation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtvslo.si/zdravje/novi-koronavirus/jansa-strinjamo-se-s-pozivom-infektologov-k-zaustavitvi-javnega-zivljenja-v-sloveniji/516993|title=Jan\u0161a: Strinjamo se s pozivom infektologov k zaustavitvi javnega \u017eivljenja v Sloveniji|website=www.rtvslo.si|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March 2020 the National Assembly confirmed the list of ministers and the government took office.<ref>{{cite web|author=M. Z., Tanja Kozorog Blatnik |url=https://www.rtvslo.si/slovenija/jansa-zavrnil-govorice-o-karanteni-smiselna-je-le-samokarantena/517026 |title=Jan\u0161a zavrnil govorice o karanteni: \"Smiselna je le samokarantena\" |publisher=Rtvslo.Si |date=2019-09-20 |accessdate=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n=== Election of the Prime Minister ===\nPrime Minister is elected by the National Assembly with majority of all votes. Candidate is proposed by the President of the Republic (1st, 2nd and 3rd round) or by MPs (2nd and 3rd round only). If Prime Minister is not elected in the first two rounds, the National Assembly can decide with relative majority of votes, to hold the third round, where only relative majority is needed to elect Prime Minister.<ref>Constitution of the Republic of Slovenia, Article 111.</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+\n!Date\n!Candidate\n!Proposer\n!In favor\n!Against\n!Invalid\n!Note\n!Source\n|-\n|3 March 2020\n|'''[[Janez Jan\u0161a]]'''\n|President of the Republic\n| style=\"background:#9bf796;\" |'''52'''\n|31\n|1\n|Secret ballot, absolute majority (46 votes) needed\n|<ref name=\":0\" />\n|}\n=== Government confirmation vote ===\nAfter being elected Prime Minister-elect proposes his government to the National Assembly. Government is elected with relative majority. Only after the government is elected and sworn-in, Prime Minister and ministers take their offices. Swearing-in ceremony takes place immediately after the vote.<ref>Constitution of the Republic of Slovenia, Articles 112 and 113.</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Government\n!Prime Minister-elect\n!In favor\n!Against\n!Abstain\n!Note\n!Source\n|-\n|13 March 2020\n|'''14th - Jan\u0161a III'''\n|[[Janez Jan\u0161a]]\n| style=\"background:#9bf796;\" |'''52'''\n|31\n|1\n|Roll call, relative majority needed\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.24ur.com/novice/slovenija/po-zaslisanjih-zadnjih-ministrskih-kandidatov-sledi-potrjevanje-nove-vlade.html|title=DZ potrdil tretjo Jan\u0161evo vlado, ministri po prisegi \u017ee na prvi seji|website=www.24ur.com|language=sl|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Cabinet==\n{{refimprove section|date=March 2020}}\nCabinet level positions are those of Prime Minister, ministers and ministers without portfolio.<ref>{{cite web|author=La. Da. |url=https://www.rtvslo.si/slovenija/nekateri-ministri-posle-predali-z-rokovanjem-drugi-s-trkom-komolcev/517154 |title=Nekateri ministri posle predali z rokovanjem, drugi s trkom komolcev |publisher=Rtvslo.Si |date=2019-09-20 |accessdate=2020-03-14}}</ref> Others are present at the cabinet meetings (e.g. Chief of Staff to the Prime Minister, Secretary-General of the Government, Head of the Government Legal Service, state secretaries in the Office of the Prime Minister etc.). State secretaries can substitute ministers when absent. If Prime Minister is absent, he is substituted by one of the ministers, usually one of those holding the unofficial title of Deputy Prime Minister. Cabinet usually takes decisions by consensus, but it can also decide with relative majority of votes.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+\n! Name\n! Position\n! colspan=\"2\" |Party\n! Took office\n|-\n| '''[[Janez Jan\u0161a]]'''<br><small>(born 1958)</small>\n| [[Prime Minister of Slovenia|Prime Minister]]\n| style=\"background:{{Slovenian Democratic Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| '''<small>SDS</small>'''\n|13 March 2020\n|-\n| '''[[Zdravko Po\u010dival\u0161ek]]'''<br><small>(born 1957)</small>\n| Deputy Prime Minister<br>Minister of Economic Development and Technology\n| style=\"background:{{Party of Miro Cerar/meta/color}};\" |\n| '''<small>SMC</small>'''\n|13 March 2020\n|-\n| '''[[Matej Tonin]]'''<br><small>(born 1983)</small>\n| Deputy Prime Minister<br>Minister of Defence\n| style=\"background:{{New Slovenia/meta/color}}\" |\n| '''<small>NSi</small>'''\n|13 March 2020\n|-\n| '''[[Aleksandra Pivec]]'''<br><small>(born 1972)</small>\n| Deputy Prime Minister<br>Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Food\n| style=\"background:{{Democratic Party of Pensioners of Slovenia/meta/color}};\" |\n| '''<small>DeSUS</small>'''\n|13 March 2020\n|-\n| '''[[Simona Kustec Lipicer]]'''<br><small>(born 1976)</small>\n| Minister of Education, Science and Sport\n| style=\"background:{{Party of Miro Cerar/meta/color}};\" |\n| '''<small>SMC</small>'''\n|13 March 2020\n|-\n| '''[[Janez Cigler Kralj]]'''<br><small>(born 1978)</small>\n| Minister of Labour, Family, Social Affairs and Equal Opportunity\n| style=\"background:{{New Slovenia/meta/color}}\" |\n| '''<small>NSi</small>'''\n|13 March 2020\n|-\n| '''[[Jernej Vrtovec]]'''<br><small>(born 1985)</small>\n| Minister of Infrastructure\n| style=\"background:{{New Slovenia/meta/color}}\" |\n| '''<small>NSi</s