{"title_page": "Vavoom!", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Vavoom!\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[The Brian Setzer Orchestra]]\n| cover      = Vavoom.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = August 1, 2000\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Swing revival]], [[jump blues]], [[rock and roll]]\n| length     = 43:18\n| label      = [[Interscope]]\n| producer   = [[Glen Ballard]], [[Peter Collins (record producer)|Peter Collins]], [[Dave Darling]]\n| prev_title = [[The Dirty Boogie]]\n| prev_year  = 1998\n| next_title = [[Jumpin' East of Java]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|2.5|5}}<ref>{{AllMusic | class=album | id=vavoom!-mw0001952421 | title=''The Brian Setzer Orchestra: Vavoom!'' | first=Stephen Thomas | last=Erlewine | accessdate=April 29, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Vavoom!''''' is the fourth studio album by the [[swing music|swing]] band [[The Brian Setzer Orchestra]]. It was released in 2000 on [[Interscope Records]].\n\n==Track listing==\nAll tracks composed by Brian Setzer; except where indicated.\n\n# \"[[Pennsylvania 6-5000 (song)|Pennsylvania 6-5000]]\" (Setzer, Bill Finegan, Jerry Gray, Carl Sigman, Mike Himelstein)\n# \"Jumpin' East of Java\"\n# \"[[Tu Vu\u00f2 F\u00e0 L'Americano|Americano]]\" (Setzer, [[Renato Carosone]])\n# \"If You Can't Rock Me\"\n# \"Gettin' [[In the Mood]]\" (Mike Himelstein)\n# \"Drive Like Lightning (Crash Like Thunder)\" (Setzer, Mark Winchester)\n# \"[[Mack the Knife]]\" ([[Marc Blitzstein]], [[Kurt Weill]], [[Bertolt Brecht]])\n# \"[[Caravan (1937 song)|Caravan]]\" ([[Irving Mills]], [[Duke Ellington]], [[Juan Tizol]])\n# \"The Footloose Doll\"\n# \"From Here to Eternity\" (Setzer, Rick Bell)\n# \"That's the Kind of Sugar Papa Likes\"\n# \"'49 Mercury Blues\"\n# \"Jukebox\"\n# \"Gloria\" (Esther Navarro)\n# \"[[Rock-A-Beatin' Boogie]]\" ([[Bill Haley (musician)|Bill Haley]]) (Japan only bonus track)\n\n==Personnel==\n*Brian Setzer - [[Jazz guitar|guitar]], [[Singing|vocals]]\n*[[Bernie Dresel]] - [[Drum kit|drums]], [[Percussion instrument|percussion]]\n*Ray Hermann - [[saxophone]]\n*George McMullen - [[trombone]]\n*Tim Misica - saxophone\n*Mark Winchester - [[Double bass|bass]]\n*Robbie Hioki - trombone\n*Kevin Norton - [[trumpet]]\n*Mike Himelstein - [[Backing vocalist|background vocals]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{The Brian Setzer Orchestra}}\n\n[[Category:The Brian Setzer Orchestra albums]]\n[[Category:2000 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Glen Ballard]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Peter Collins (record producer)]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Dave Darling]]\n[[Category:Interscope Records albums]]\n\n\n{{2000s-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Vavoom!\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[The Brian Setzer Orchestra]]\n| cover      = Vavoom.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = August 1, 2000\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Swing revival]], [[jump blues]], [[rock and roll]]\n| length     = 43:18\n| label      = [[Interscope]]\n| producer   = [[Glen Ballard]], [[Peter Collins (record producer)|Peter Collins]], [[Dave Darling]]\n| prev_title = [[The Dirty Boogie]]\n| prev_year  = 1998\n| next_title = [[Jumpin' East of Java]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|2.5|5}}<ref>{{AllMusic | class=album | id=vavoom!-mw0001952421 | title=''The Brian Setzer Orchestra: Vavoom! '' | first=Stephen Thomas | last=Erlewine | accessdate=April 29, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Vavoom!''''' is the fourth studio album by the [[swing music|swing]] band [[The Brian Setzer Orchestra]]. It was released in 2000 on [[Interscope Records]].\n\n==Track listing==\nAll tracks composed by Brian Setzer; except where indicated.\n\n# \"[[Pennsylvania 6-5000 (song)|Pennsylvania 6-5000]]\" (Setzer, Bill Finegan, Jerry Gray, Carl Sigman, Mike Himelstein)\n# \"Jumpin' East of Java\"\n# \