{"title_page": "National Games of China", "text_new": "{{Infobox sporting event organization\n|name         = National Games of the People's Republic of China<br>\u4e2d\u534e\u4eba\u6c11\u5171\u548c\u56fd\u5168\u56fd\u8fd0\u52a8\u4f1a\n|image        = AllChinaGamesFlag.svg\n|caption      =\n|image2       = \n|size2        = \n|caption2     = \n|abbreviation = National Games of the PRC; All China Games \n|motto        = \n|formation    = 1959\n|recurrence   = 4 years\n|last         = \n|purpose      = Sports for elite athletes in [[People's Republic of China|China]]\n|headquarters = \n|leader_title = \n|leader_name  = \n|website      ={{url|en.olympic.cn/games/national}} \n|remarks      =\n}}\n{{Infobox Chinese\n|showflag=stp\n|s=\u4e2d\u534e\u4eba\u6c11\u5171\u548c\u56fd\u5168\u56fd\u8fd0\u52a8\u4f1a\n|t=\u4e2d\u83ef\u4eba\u6c11\u5171\u548c\u570b\u5168\u570b\u904b\u52d5\u6703\n|p=Zh\u014dnghu\u00e1 R\u00e9nm\u00edn G\u00f2ngh\u00e9gu\u00f3 Qu\u00e1ngu\u00f3 Y\u00f9nd\u00f2nghu\u00ec\n|w=Chunghua Jenmin Kunghekuo Ch'\u00fcankuo Y\u00fcntunghui\n}}\n\nThe '''National Games of the People's Republic of China''', sometimes known as the '''All China Games''' (though not to be confused with the [[All-China Games]]), is the premier sports event in [[China]] at national level. It is usually held once every four years, most recently in August 2017, when the [[2017 National Games of China|13th National Games of China]] took place in [[Tianjin]]. \n\nThe forerunner of the Games was the '''Chinese National Games''', first held in 1910 during the [[Qing dynasty]]. This tournament ran until 1948 and the competition was relaunched under its current name in 1959, following the [[history of the People's Republic of China|formation of the People's Republic of China]].<ref>[http://www.gbrathletics.com/nc/chn.htm Chinese National Games]. GBR Athletics. Retrieved on 2009-10-24.</ref> On the other hand, the original Chinese National Games continued to be held by the [[Taiwan|Republic of China]] which is now based in [[geography of Taiwan|Taiwan]].<ref>[https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%B8%AD%E5%8D%8E%E6%B0%91%E5%9B%BD%E5%85%A8%E5%9B%BD%E8%BF%90%E5%8A%A8%E4%BC%9A \u4e2d\u534e\u6c11\u56fd\u5168\u56fd\u8fd0\u52a8\u4f1a] {{zh icon}}</ref>\n\n== List of the National Games of China ==\n{{Location map+|China|float=center|width=500|caption=Host cities of the National Games|places=\n{{Location map~|China||position=|lat=41.817651|long=123.431472|label='''[[Shenyang|2013]]'''}}\n{{Location map~|China||position=left|lat=39.909395|long=116.413938|label='''[[Beijing|1959, 1965, 1975, 1979, 1993]]'''}}\n{{Location map~|China||position=right|lat=39.099266|long=117.200983|label='''[[Tianjin|2017]]'''}}\n{{Location map~|China||position=right|lat=36.664033|long=117.120000|label='''[[Jinan|2009]]'''}}\n{{Location map~|China||position=|lat=34.266667|long=108.954000|label='''[[Xi'an|2021]]'''}}\n{{Location map~|China||position=|lat=32.076702|long=118.796877|label='''[[Nanjing|2005]]'''}}\n{{Location map~|China||position=right|lat=31.244211|long=121.473701|label='''[[Shanghai|1983, 1997]]'''}}\n{{Location map~|China||position=|lat=23.145803|long=113.277283|label='''[[Guangzhou|1987, 2001]]'''}}\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Games\n!Hosts\n!Dates\n!Teams\n!Athletes\n!Sports\n!Events\n!Ref\n|-\n|align=center|[[1959 National Games of China|I]]\n|[[Beijing|Beijing Municipality]]\n|13 September\u20133 October 1959\n|align=right|29\n|align=right|10,658\n|align=right|42\n|align=right|384\n|\n|-\n|align=center|[[1965 National Games of China|II]]\n|[[Beijing|Beijing Municipality]]\n|11\u201328 September 1965\n|align=right|29\n|align=right|5,014\n|align=right|23\n|align=right|300\n|\n|-\n|align=center|[[1975 National Games of China|III]]\n|[[Beijing|Beijing Municipality]]\n|12\u201328 September 1975\n|align=right|31\n|align=right|12,497\n|align=right|42\n|align=right|310\n|\n|-\n|align=center|[[1979 National Games of China|IV]]\n|[[Beijing|Beijing Municipality]]\n|15\u201330 